Revision history for DMS

0.3.0   2026-04-29
        - SPEC v0.14: rename DMS::Parser::parse(),
          DMS::Parser::parse_document(), DMS::Parser::parse_lite(),
          DMS::Parser::parse_lite_document(),
          DMS::Parser::parse_document_unordered() and
          DMS::Parser::parse_lite_document_unordered() to decode(),
          decode_document(), decode_lite(), decode_lite_document(),
          decode_document_unordered() and
          decode_lite_document_unordered() respectively. The old names
          remain as deprecated aliases that emit a one-time
          Carp::carp warning and forward to the new sub. The old
          names will be removed in the release after this one.
        - SPEC v0.14: rename DMS::Parser::to_dms() / ::to_dms_lite() and
          DMS::Emitter::to_dms() / ::to_dms_lite() to encode() /
          encode_lite(). Old names retained as deprecated aliases.
        - decode_front_matter() is intentionally not yet added; that
          API arrives in a follow-up release.

0.2.0   prior
        - Pre-rename baseline (parse / to_dms naming).
